The paper deals with formalizing programming language metatheory, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of Coq, a proof assistant based on the Calculus of Inductive Constructions, suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The focus on type systems and algorithmic subtyping suggests that the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category is also likely. The use of formal methods and the mention of the POPLmark Challenge suggest that the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category is relevant. The mention of encodings and abstract syntax suggests that the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category may also be relevant. Finally, the mention of type systems and formal developments suggests that the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category may be relevant as well.
